Threshold calculation for popularity¶

In [7]:
# Determining the threshold (median number of shares)
threshold = df['shares'].median()
print(f"Threshold for popularity: {threshold}")

# Creating the new column 'popularity' using pd.cut
df['popularity'] = pd.cut(
    df['shares'],
    bins=[0, threshold, df['shares'].max() + 1],  # Adding 1 to include max value in 'Popular'
    labels=['Not Popular', 'Popular'],
    include_lowest=True,
    right=False
)

# Converting 'popularity' to numeric labels for classification tasks
df['popularity_numeric'] = df['popularity'].map({'Not Popular': 0, 'Popular': 1})

Threshold for popularity: 1400.0

Dimensionality Reduction using PCA¶

In [20]:
# Defining features and classification variable
X = df_filtered.drop(['url', 'timedelta', 'shares', 'popularity', 'popularity_numeric'], axis=1)
y_classification = df_filtered['popularity_numeric']
y_regression = df_filtered['shares']
In [21]:
# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train_class, y_test_class = train_test_split(X, y_classification, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
X_train_reg, X_test_reg, y_train_reg, y_test_reg = train_test_split(X, y_regression, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Scale numerical features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_train_class_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_class_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)
X_train_reg_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_reg_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

# Dimensionality Reduction using PCA
pca = PCA(n_components=0.95)
X_train_pca_class = pca.fit_transform(X_train_class_scaled)
X_test_pca_class = pca.transform(X_test_class_scaled)
X_train_pca_reg = pca.fit_transform(X_train_reg_scaled)
X_test_pca_reg = pca.transform(X_test_reg_scaled)

Classification Tasks (Classification Report)¶

In [22]:
# Logistic Regression Classifier
logistic_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
logistic_model.fit(X_train_pca_class, y_train_class)
y_pred_logistic = logistic_model.predict(X_test_pca_class)

# Evaluating Logistic Regression model performance
logistic_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test_class, y_pred_logistic)
logistic_precision = precision_score(y_test_class, y_pred_logistic)
logistic_recall = recall_score(y_test_class, y_pred_logistic)
logistic_f1 = f1_score(y_test_class, y_pred_logistic)

# Calculate metrics for each model
models = ['Logistic Regression', 'Random Forest', 'Gradient Boosting', 'SVC', 'MLP']
y_preds = [y_pred_logistic, y_pred_rf, y_pred_gb, y_pred_svc, y_pred_mlp]

precision_scores = [precision_score(y_test_class, y_pred) for y_pred in y_preds]
recall_scores = [recall_score(y_test_class, y_pred) for y_pred in y_preds]
f1_scores = [f1_score(y_test_class, y_pred) for y_pred in y_preds]
accuracy_scores = [accuracy_score(y_test_class, y_pred) for y_pred in y_preds]

# Store metrics in a DataFrame
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Model': models,
    'Precision': precision_scores,
    'Recall': recall_scores,
    'F1-score': f1_scores,
    'Accuracy': accuracy_scores
})

# Plot the metrics
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

plt.plot(metrics_df['Model'], metrics_df['Precision'], label='Precision', marker='o')
plt.plot(metrics_df['Model'], metrics_df['Recall'], label='Recall', marker='o')
plt.plot(metrics_df['Model'], metrics_df['F1-score'], label='F1-score', marker='o')
plt.plot(metrics_df['Model'], metrics_df['Accuracy'], label='Accuracy', marker='o')

plt.title('Classification Metrics Comparison')
plt.xlabel('Model')
plt.ylabel('Metric Value')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Function to display confusion matrix and count plot
def display_confusion_matrix_and_count_plot(comparison_df, model_name):
    # Confusion Matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(comparison_df["Actual"], comparison_df.iloc[:, 1])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Not Popular', 'Popular'], yticklabels=['Not Popular', 'Popular'])
    plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix for {model_name}')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('Actual')
    plt.show()

    # Count Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    sns.countplot(data=comparison_df, x='Actual', hue=comparison_df.columns[1], palette='Set2')
    plt.title(f'{model_name} Predictions vs Actual')
    plt.xlabel('Actual')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Predicted')
    plt.show()

# Function to Display ROC curves for each model
def display_roc_curve(comparison_df, model_name, y_pred_proba):
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(comparison_df["Actual"], y_pred_proba[:,1])
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color='blue', lw=2, label=f'{model_name} (area = %0.2f)' % roc_auc)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='red', lw=2, linestyle='--')
    plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title(f'Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve for {model_name}')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()
